🧬 Project Seed: "USF Beacon" (P2P Social Orchestration)
Project Goal: A high-velocity, privacy-first mobile app for USF students to create real-time physical meetups ("Beacons") without persistent data storage or invasive tracking.

Core Tech Stack:

Frontend: Flutter (Mobile-first, declarative UI).

Backend/Realtime: Supabase (Auth, PostGIS for location, Realtime Broadcast for P2P pings).

External APIs: Gemini (Icebreaker generation), Google Maps (Native Intent via url_launcher).

Architecture Principles:

Ephemeral Data: Meetups and Pings are transient. No long-term chat history.

RSI-Friendly UI: High-contrast, large touch targets, and minimal typing (Chips/Sliders over Text Fields).

Quirky Aesthetic: "Monster" profile icons (DiceBear API) and animated mascots instead of photos.

Spatial Logic: Use PostGIS geography types for distance-based filtering (Radius: 500m).

Key Data Objects:

Profile: id, username, major, coords (geography), socials (jsonb), is_online.

Meetup: creator_id, topic, tag (Study/Social), max_people, status (pending/active).

Interaction Flow:

Discovery: StreamBuilder watches profiles and meetups tables.

Handshake: Peer A sends a Supabase Broadcast (Ping) -> Peer B receives a Local Notification.

Connection: On "Accept," Gemini generates a prompt -> Trigger url_launcher to Google Maps coordinates.

My database schema is just a single SQL table called profiles. There is:

- a primary key of the ID, which is a type of UID for each user
- updated_at, which is a timestamp
- a unique username, which is text
- campus_location, which is text
- interest, which is an array of text
- online, which is a boolean
- friends, which is an array of UUIDs
- location_history, which is a binary JSON mapping each previous location to the number of times that the user has been there. For this one, only include the locations that the user has been to.
- socials, which is a binary JSON mapping each type of social, which is an enumerated type (meaning that there's only a set number of social types, not left up to the user). The value type is just a link
- is_real_name_public, which is a boolean and determines whether the user wants to show their real name or whether they just want to show their username only

